## Why This Is Asked

This angle tests robustness of an event-driven payments pipeline, focusing on idempotency, end-to-end correctness, and resilience under partial failures. It mirrors real-world fintech and high‑throughput marketplaces where retries and outbox patterns are essential.

## Key Concepts

- Idempotency keys and exactly-once semantics in asynchronous flows
- Outbox pattern, event bus (Kafka), and compensating actions
- Fault injection, timeouts, retries, and observability

## Code Example

